==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Predestination
<hw>Pre*des`ti*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praedestinatio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧destination</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
predestinating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Predestination</qex> had overruled their will.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>The purpose of Good from
eternity respecting all events; especially, the preordination of men to
everlasting happiness or misery. See <er>Calvinism</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predestinative</ent>⟦br⟧
